In this speech delivered at Carnegie Hall in New York, Vice President Kamala Harris acknowledges various dignitaries in attendance and expresses gratitude to Reverend Al Sharpton for his leadership and friendship. She highlights the importance of continuing to fight for change in the country, particularly at this pivotal moment in history. The Vice President emphasizes the need to address systemic inequities and outlines the Build Back Better framework, which focuses on equity in economic policy, affordable housing, environmental justice, and investment in historically black colleges and universities (HBCUs). She also emphasizes the importance of voting rights and urges the passing of the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. The Vice President encourages everyone to keep fighting for economic justice, voting rights, police reform, and environmental justice, emphasizing the role of collective action in achieving these goals. She concludes by emphasizing the importance of activism and participation in democracy.